    "tag_list": null,
    "overview": "<p>Front-End Web Developer with a strong focus on CSS and web standards. Areas of specific interest include user-centered design and development of accessible and usable web interfaces.</p>\n\n<p>Passion for current trends and best practices in front-end architecture, including performance, accessibility, usability, HTML5/CSS3.</p>\n\n<p>Excellent knowledge of W3C Web standards based coding. Use of semantic markup for structure, with advanced CSS for presentation and unobtrusive DOM scripting for behaviour. Quality focussed approach utilising ‘Progressive Enhancement’ techniques.</p>\n\n<p>Hand coding (X)HTML and CSS, in depth Knowledge of cross browser/platform rendering issues and CSS workaround’s. Experienced in developing content that is compliant with WAI WCAG guidelines; priority 1, 2 and 3 accessibility checkpoints. Experience of e-GIF, compliance and e-GMS metadata standards. Good knowledge of javaScript and DOM Scripting techniques to manipulate dynamic UI elements.</p>\n\n<p>Experienced at integrating front-end code with server-side technology on large-scale, dynamic website&#8217;s using MVC frameworks and templating languages.</p>\n\n<p>Specialties:Standards Based front-end development: HTML5, XHTML, HTML, CSS, CSS2.1, CSS3, Semantic Markup, W3C, Web Standards, Microformats, XML, XSLT, WAI, Accessibility, Usability, JavaScript, JQuery, DOM, AJAX, Web Design, Information Architecture, Interaction Design, User Experience Design, Front-End Architecture, Content Management, ExpressionEngine</p>",
