    "overview": "<p>Esten Hurtle is a web developer focused on building rich, cross-platform webapps using the latest in open-source technology. Focusing primarily on backend development in Python (with experience in both the Tornado and Django frameworks), he has built applications for everything from open-source projects to enterprise-class systems on the University of Missouri campus. While Python is his specialty, Esten also has considerable experience in PHP.</p>\n\n<p>In addition to backend work, Esten is also an experienced front-end developer, working with AJAX and JavaScript to ensure a seamless user experience across multiple platforms. In 2010, Esten was the front-end developer for a winning team in the Interaction Design contest sponsored by Adobe, the Reynolds Journalism Institute at the University of Missouri, and Hearst Innovation.</p>\n\n<p>Currently, he is working as a developer for LearningWeb, an e-learning startup based in Columbia, MO.</p>",
