    "twitter": "dardawk",
    "tag_list": "web-developer, asp-net, mvc, microsoft, ux, ui, front-end-developer",
    "overview": "<p>Dominik is a web developer on the Microsoft stack focusing (currently) on front-end and ASP.NET MVC. </p>\n\n<p>From his blog:\n&#8220;I&#8217;m a web developer for TC Media, a marketing company in Canada. I’m based out of London, Ontario where I live, work, and play. I specialize in front-end development, but I have extensive server-side experience with the Microsoft Web stack.&#8221;</p>\n\n<p>&#8220;My strongest experience is with ASP.NET C# (web forms and MVC), and JavaScript, HTML/5, and CSS/3.&#8221;</p>\n\n<p>&#8220;I love learning new things, which is why I test drove so many frameworks and programming languages:</p>\n\n<ul>\n<li>Java EE – In my previous position, I worked with Oracle and Java. It’s a great technology, and I enjoyed working with it.</li>\n<li>PHP\\MySql (this blog) – I created a custom theme for this website, my wedding RSVP site, and some other random crap. Although I have to use it because all cheap shared hosting uses the LAMP stack, I hate it. Every time I program with it, I miss being coddled by visual studio and Microsoft’s proven frameworks.</li>\n<li>Ruby on Rails – random experimentation. Couldn’t get used to it.</li>\n<li>node.js – experimented with it to create an art project.</li>\n<li>Flash ActionScript – created the front end of my wedding RSVP website as well as projects for work.</li>\n<li>Silverlight and WPF – worked with it at my current position</li>\n<li>C++, C, Python, PowerShell, VB Script&#8221;</li>\n</ul>",
    "image": "http://crunchbase.com/assets/images/resized/0027/4833/274833v2-max-150x150.png",
