    "twitter": "jontroutman",
    "tag_list": "",
    "overview": "<p>Jon is a product designer with ux/ui, interaction, and front-end skills and a core depth in bridging online and offline user experiences.</p>\n\n<p>He was one of the initial team members at General Assembly (Oct 2011 – June 2013) where he led product design helping GA scale from a single community of users in NYC to a global network of campuses + online educational content provider. Jon is also an enthusiastic front-end developer who recognizes the relationship between clean code and good UX. While at GA, he wrote code and collaborated with the engineering team to rebuild General Assembly&#8217;s website with a content-focused, mobile-first approach.</p>\n\n<p>In 2012 Jon cofounded Designer&#8217;s Debate Club — an ongoing bare-knuckled, bow-tied, oxford-style-debate event series (started in NYC, expanding to more cities).</p>\n\n<p>Jon is currently Cofounder / Creative Director at Canary.</p>",
